### E-Tube Streaming Platform API Testing Suite

@host = http://localhost:8080
@videoId = 1

### 1. Upload Video
# Uploads a video file along with title and description.
# Note: sample.mp4 is located in the same directory as this file.
POST {{host}}/api/videos/upload
Content-Type: multipart/form-data; boundary=WebAppBoundary

--WebAppBoundary
Content-Disposition: form-data; name="file"; filename="sample.mp4"
Content-Type: video/mp4

< ./sample.mp4
--WebAppBoundary
Content-Disposition: form-data; name="title"

E-Tube Concurrent Streaming Demo
--WebAppBoundary
Content-Disposition: form-data; name="description"

Demonstrating high concurrency streaming with Spring Boot, Redis, and RabbitMQ.
--WebAppBoundary--


### 2. Get All Videos
# Lists metadata of all uploaded videos from PostgreSQL.
GET {{host}}/api/videos
Accept: application/json


### 3. Get Video Details by ID (First Hit - Cache Miss)
# Queries PostgreSQL. Logs will show "Cache miss: Fetching video details from PostgreSQL".
GET {{host}}/api/videos/{{videoId}}
Accept: application/json


### 4. Get Video Details by ID (Second Hit - Cache Hit)
# Queries Redis. No SQL logs will be printed. Very low latency response.
GET {{host}}/api/videos/{{videoId}}
Accept: application/json


### 5. Stream Video - Initial Chunk (No Range Header)
# Streams the first segment of the video (up to 1MB).
GET {{host}}/api/videos/{{videoId}}/stream
Accept: video/mp4


### 6. Stream Video - Seek Range (Bytes 0-100)
# Simulates player requesting the first 101 bytes. Response will be 206 Partial Content.
GET {{host}}/api/videos/{{videoId}}/stream
Range: bytes=0-100
Accept: video/mp4


### 7. Stream Video - Seek Range (Bytes 101-300)
# Simulates seeking to a mid-point in the video.
GET {{host}}/api/videos/{{videoId}}/stream
Range: bytes=101-300
Accept: video/mp4


### 8. Post a Comment to the Video (Stored in MongoDB)
# Saves user feedback to MongoDB for high throughput write scaling.
POST {{host}}/api/videos/{{videoId}}/comments
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "author": "TechVlogger",
  "content": "This byte-range streaming works seamlessly! Great stuff."
}


### 9. Get Comments for the Video
# Fetches all comments from MongoDB sorted by creation time.
GET {{host}}/api/videos/{{videoId}}/comments
Accept: application/json


### 10. Record a Video View (Asynchronous Event-Driven Integration)
# Triggers a view log. Returns 202 Accepted immediately without database blockages.
# RabbitMQ will process this to increment views in SQL and write logs to MongoDB.
POST {{host}}/api/videos/{{videoId}}/view


### 11. Get Video Details (Verify incremented views)
# Re-fetches details to observe the updated view count (cache is evicted automatically).
GET {{host}}/api/videos/{{videoId}}
Accept: application/json
